text.paragraph:
Macitentan tablets are contraindicated for use during pregnancy because it may cause fetal harm based on animal data [see Contraindications (

4.1), Warnings and Precautions (
5.1

)], Use in Specific Populations (8.1
   )].

Strong inducers of CYP3A4 such as rifampin significantly reduce macitentan exposure. Concomitant use of macitentan tablets with strong CYP3A4 inducers should be avoided [see Clinical Pharmacology (


                              12.3


                              )].
